statement.p:
Let D be the closure of an open set U in \mathbb{R}^2 and orient D with the standard orientation \tder{}{x} \wedge \tder{}{y}. Suppose p is on the boundary \partial D, \nu is the dual of the normal vector \mb{n} pointing outward, and \mb{T} is the unit tangent vector of \partial D positively pairs with the orientation \vol^{\partial D}. Since 

                \vol^D = \vol^{st} = \tder{}{x} \wedge \tder{}{y}

                we must have that \mb{T} is a \pi / 2 counter-clockwise rotation of \mb{n} to ensure that \vol^D = \nu \wedge \vol^{\partial D}.

For any positive real number R let

                   S^{n - 1} (R) = \{ (x_1, \ldots, x_n) \in \mathbb{R}^{n -  1} : x_1^2 + \cdots + x_n^2 = R^2 \}

                   be the (n - 1)-dimensional sphere of radius R. Let 

                   \eta = \sum_{i = 1}^n (-1)^{i - 1} \frac{x_i \, \tder{}{x_1} \wedge \cdots \wedge \tder{}{x_{i - 1}} \wedge \tder{}{x_{i + 1}} \wedge \cdots \wedge \tder{}{x_n}}{(x_1^2 + \cdots + x_n^2)^{\frac{n}{2}}}

                   and show that, for any R_1 and R_2

                   \int_{S^{n - 1} (R_1)} \eta = \int_{S^{n - 1} (R_2)} \eta.
